## SignUP

Signing up with Cashleo has been made simple and first. Takes less than 10mins

** For Individuals **
Head over to www.app.ugmart.ug
Fill in your personal details, username and password
A follow up email will be sent to request for your identification original scanned copy (National ID, Passport or Driving license)
But even before, your account will be activated instantly and start transacting.

** For Businesses **
To sign up, visit www.app.ugmart.ug
Register and fill in the business details.
A follow up email will be sent to request for your business registration details
But even before, your account will be activated instantly and start transacting.

Integrating your website/ app with Cashleo
To integrate Cashleo into your website, it takes 3 simple steps.

1_	Log into your website backend
2_	If on WordPress, install and activate the woocashleo plugin for business and for donations, please install and activate the cashleo give plugin. (if not on WordPress, feature for you, comming soon)
3_	Go to the both plugin settings pages, and fill in your individual/business details got from www.app.ugmart.ug

Or Simply follow this tutorial. (Post or video link)



## FAQ


1.	How do I register
Simply go to app.ugmart.ug and sign up. You’ll get app login details that you’ll fill into your website (plugin settings) dashboard. This process takes less than 10 mins and is instant.

2.	What are your charges on receiving money
For momo payments, we charge 3.5% per transaction. For card payments……??

3.	What are your charges on withdrawing money
We don’t change any money when withdrawing

4.	Can I pay for utilities using my ugmart balance
Yes, you simply login to your ugmart merchant account. www.app.ugmart.ug

5.	Do you offer free support
Yes, both via phone and ticket.

6.	What documents are needed for small business to start receiving funds using your platform?
For an individual, we only need a scanner copy of (original) your National ID, Password copy or Driving license.

7.	Which website platforms do you support?
At the moment, we only support WordPress and or Woocommerce enabled websites.

8.	Can I use my WordPress Website to receive funds
Yes. We have also built a seamless plugin just for this. Very powerful and works like charm.

9.	Can I receive donations for my cause or for our church?
Yes.

10.	Which payment methods do you support?
We accept mobile money and card payments. (Visa and Master card)

11.	Are your services FREE
Yes, using our platform is free of charge. We only levy you once you make any transaction.

12.	How different are you from your competitors?
We pride our selves in using technology to bring change and impart our community through building tools that enable them leave and perform better. PayMartUG is just one of that.
Also, we are the only gateway locally that enables you to receive donations for any of your causes seamlessly.

13.	What does momo mean?
Mobile Money alias MoMo

14.	Does my client have to register with UGMart
No, your client simply has to pay using their credit/debit card or mobile money

15.	How long does it take to get receive or withdraw my money.
All momo transcations are instant. For bank transfers, it will take minimum 3 business days for money to reflect on your account.

16.	Why should I trust using your services
We are a legally operating business with physical address registered under the Uganda company act. Also all your transactions are safe and secure with our PCI compliance certification.

17.	What kind of persons /business can use your platform
Both individuals, businesses and charities are welcome.

18.	What currencies do you support
At the moment, we only support Uganda shillings. But your client can pay in any currency they wish like.

19.	Can I pay bills and utilities?
Yes, you can literally pay for any utilities and bills using our platform. (Water, Yaka, Tax, Statelite TV etc)

